  "prompt": "How do I make friend?",
  "response": "Making friends can be challenging, but here are some tips to help you:\n\n1. Be open and approachable\n- Smile and maintain positive body language\n- Show genuine interest in others\n\n2. Join social groups or clubs\n- Sports teams\n- Hobby groups\n- Classes or workshops\n- Volunteer organizations\n\n3. Use social platforms\n- Meetup apps\n- Social media groups\n- Online communities with shared interests\n\n4. Practice good conversation skills\n- Ask open-ended questions\n- Listen actively\n- Share about yourself\n- Show empathy\n\n5. Attend social events\n- Parties\n- Community gatherings\n- Workplace or school events\n\n6. Be consistent\n- Follow up after meeting someone\n- Suggest hanging out\n- Stay in touch\n\n7. Be yourself\n- Don't try to change who you are\n- Show your authentic personality\n\n8. Be patient\n- Building friendships takes time\n- Don't get discouraged\n\n9. Work on self-confidence\n- Believe in yourself\n- Develop your interests and skills\n\n10. Practice social skills\n- Start with small interactions\n- Gradually build your comfort level\n\nRemember, quality matters more than quantity when it comes to friendships.",
